</taxonomicName>
. Both sexes have a yellow metasoma and terga with apical hair bands (see diagnosis and description). This combination of characters is unique in 
<taxonomicName id="A5E74D2CE24FFF86FCBCFB28FBFBFB1D" authorityName="Popov" authorityYear="1940" box="[934,1092,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Eremaphanta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5093EABDE24FFF86FCBCFB28FBFBFB1D" box="[934,1092,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="56">Eremaphanta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="625836AFE24FFF86FE22FB00FBCAFB74" blockId="9.[264,1323,839,1905]" box="[312,1141,1199,1225]" pageId="9" pageNumber="56">
Etymology. Named in honour of 
<collectionCode id="04F6AE6AE24FFF86FDA1FB00FD6FFB74" box="[699,720,1199,1225]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="9" pageNumber="56" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode id="04F6AE6AE24FFF86FDC0FB00FD50FB74" box="[730,751,1199,1225]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="9" pageNumber="56" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. Popov who described the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="625836AFE24FFF86FE22FB78FCA3FAA4" blockId="9.[264,1323,839,1905]" pageId="9" pageNumber="56">
Differential diagnosis. 
<specimenCount id="74E1FD26E24FFF86FD52FB79FDE3FB57" box="[584,604,1238,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="56" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="74E1FD26E24FFF86FD8CFB77FD18FB57" box="[662,679,1240,1258]" pageId="9" pageNumber="56" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Close to 
<taxonomicName id="A5E74D2CE24FFF86FC3BFB78FC2BFB4D" authorityName="Popov 1957: 1706 -" authorityYear="1707" box="[801,916,1239,1264]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Eremaphanta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="5093EABDE24FFF86FC3BFB78FC2BFB4D" box="[801,916,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="56">E. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Body mainly yellow. Head about as long as wide. Terga with apical hair bands.
</paragraph>
